THIS IS A BEAUTIFUL, HIGHLY DESIRED DARK WOOD KIMBER MODEL 82 GOVERNMENT  RIFLE

Not to say that under a magnifying light, they could not be distinguished as blemishes to the wood. Considering the way these were handled in the 90’s under inventory control. This one is very nice. Bolt and Rifle serial numbers match and this one is GM001xxx.

I hand picked and purchased several of these rifles in August and the first one I used was a good shooter, so I am going to sell a couple of them. 

I will transfer the rifle at this point, one of three ways. I will ship to your FFL dealer if they will receive from an individual. I can legally ship person to person using USPS within the state of Florida ONLY.  Buyer is responsible for all shipping cost. Cost within the state is $30 insured and priority 2nd Day.

Some information in regards to the Kimber Model 82 Government Rifle:
http://www.odcmp.com/Sales/kimber82desc.htm

If you have a gunsmith disassemble, add the available replacement trigger spring (which goes with the rifle), and hone and polish both the trigger foot and sear. title: For Sale:  THREE Springfield M1a Rifles -  Vintage production from G.I. M14s
postcontent:
Where: Austin Area
Prices: ~ $2000 each, depending on options and accessories you want included. Two are unfired (aside from proof firing), pre-ban rifles.
How: FTF in Central Texas, maybe DFW area
Message me for details and to schedule inspection. 
Serious inquiries only, please. CASH. 

CLICK LINK FOR PIC: https://fbcdn-sphotos-g-a.akamaihd.net/hphotos-ak-ash4/998955_REDACTED3049538_315274043_n.jpg

First, for those that don't know, these are far more desirable than current production rifles because they are all three built from USGI M14 select-fire rifles from government arsenals. They are predominantly GI parts of a superior grade to the commercial parts used in the modern M1a. They include parts from the original Springfield armory (not the Inc.), TRW and H&R. Two are in GI fiberglass stocks that are much stiffer than the polymer used today. One is in a GI type walnut stock that is a civilian replacement. It is very nice. All are suitable for shooting, collecting or custom builds. There is no better hog gun!

All three are caliber 7.62mm x 51mm (.308 Win), headspaced by SAI to shoot both. It is impossible to convert these back to select-fire, though dummy selector kits allow you to make it appear that way. The first two are pre-ban rifles that still have the bayonet lugs. All three have chrome lined barrels. Each will include a modern GI magazine, and I have a few extras that we might work into the deal.
I am only selling two. The last of the three will be saved for a custom build.

#1- Serial number 073xxx, converted by SAI in 1993 or 1994, G.I. fiberglass stock with trap-door butt plate used in early production (stores cleaning kit and for shouldering with grenade launcher), selector cut-outs have not been filled, TRW bolt, M1 Garand type rear sight with locking bar, this rifle is unfired except for proof firing. That would have been 2 rounds at SAI, and 2 rounds by me. No magazine was loaded and you can see zero wear internally.

#2- Serial number 077xxx, converted by SAI in 1993 or 1994, G.I. fiberglass stock with rubber butt plate used in late production, selector cut-outs HAVE been filled, SA bolt, M14 rear sight, this rifle is unfired except for proof firing. That would have been 2 rounds at SAI, and 2 rounds by me. No magazine was loaded and you can see zero wear internally.

#3- Serial number 086xxx, converted by SAI in late 1994, G.I. type walnut stock with trap-door butt plate used in early production (stores cleaning kit and for shouldering with grenade launcher), selector cut-outs were never cut in this replacement stock, TRW bolt, M14 rear sight , this rifle has a VERY low round count, perhaps 60. It has almost no wear internally. No bayonet lug, as this one was produced immediately after the 1994 AWB went into effect. It includes a GI web sling. This is the gun I selected to customize. It will be the most expensive of the three because it has a high number of TRW parts.

The optics are not for sale, but I can tell you where the best price is. (this means I may sell them, but not at a loss)

I also have an extra TRW barrel with complete GI gas system from my last build. $350 It was grouping 1.5 MOA when I pulled it to install a new barrel. It has had about 300 rounds through it. The bore is chrome lined with no measurable erosion or flaking of the chrome.

title: For Sale:  Springfield Armory M1 Garand Package
postcontent:
Just found out I'm gonna be a dad. Gonna sell a few things to pay off some bills we accumulated buying 40 acres and a house a three months ago. Great timing, huh?

This is the ultimate  SA M1 Garand package (gun, gear, and 504 rounds). It shoots great (tears up a 2 liter Coke bottle at 100 yards with Greek surplus). This gun, judging by serial numbers and parts, definitely saw action in World War II and Korea. Gun is in great shape with a conservative 85% finish and no rusting.

Though it's a service gun, it is ALL Springfield Armory from what I can tell. That's hard to find on a service gun since most were rearsenalled with a mismatch of parts after WWII. Stock was refinished or replaced at some point (no cartouches), but appears to have the original wood on top of the barrel. The lack of cartouches is common on replacement stocks sent abroad.

Bullet still sits in the muzzle with the proper 1/16"+ gap between bullet and brass. Again, this is a tack driver for a 67 year old gun with a 59 year old barrel!

I did install a Schuster adjustable gas plug recently to reduce operating pressures. It cycles Greek HXP just fine. Comes with the original gas plug as well.

Receiver: SA (January 1944)
Bolt: SA (Revision 19 [Post November 1944])
Barrel: SA (December 1952)
Trigger Guard: SA (Type 1 [Pre 1944])
Op Rod: SA (Post WWII production [Older ones cracked after repeated use. Probably put in when rebarreled])

$1000 Local. $1100 Trade or Non-Local with me driving [U]at least[/U] half way to meet you. Depends on what we can work out, but I prefer local. 

ONLY trade interests would be a stainless XDs in 9mm or a Sig P290 (stainless) with night sights (standard or RS). Maybe a Sig P938 with NS. If you've got holsters or extra mags, we can work something out. Don't care if the XDs is a recall gun and hasn't been back.

PACKAGE INCLUDES:
Gun
Period correct rifle sling
Schuster adjustable gas plug and original
288 rounds on Greek HXP Bandoleers (Greek HXP) with cans (No longer available from the CMP)
120 rounds in loose enbloc clips (Greek HXP)
64 loose rounds of Greek HXP
32 rounds of 165gr Federal Deer Thugs
1 empty bandoleer with cardboard
40-50 empty brass (HXP and Federal)
Black plastic ammo case

That's the gun, the cans, and 504 rounds of ammo.

Live in Springfield. Work in downtown Savannah.
